interface: change pointopoint short flag from P to p

The P short flag was used by IFF_POINTOPOINT and IFF_PROMISC.  Change
IFF_POINTOPOINT to use p to avoid confusion, and because IFF_PROMISC
is probably more common for people to check.

README/INSTALL: refresh for the modern times

Drop all discussion of kernels older than Linux 2.6.  That was first
released ~16 years ago at this point, so we probably don't need to
cater to Linux 2.4 users (last release 10 years ago) or Linux 2.2 or
2.0 users (last releases 16 years ago).

Drop all discussion of glibc versions.  The glibc 2.0/2.2 and libc5
stuff happened so long ago that new users have no idea what they
mean.  Lets focus on modern topics like being "POSIX compliant".

THANKS: add a few more people from `git-log`

And update the mailing list contact while we're here.

netstat: Set SCTP report compliant with -l/--listening option.

'netstat -S' should give only active SCTP connections,
'netstat -Sl' should give only SCTP servers and
'netstat -Sa' should give both.

build: drop support for backing up programs

This hasn't worked since ifconfig & route moved from /sbin to /bin,
and hasn't stayed up-to-date with other programs being added.  Plus,
it's a bit racy as described in bug #38 since it runs in parallel
with the installbin target (e.g. `make install -j`).
